name: glycerophosphodiester phosphodiesterase
reaction: a glycerophosphodiester + H2O = an alcohol + sn-glycerol 3-phosphate [RN:R00857]
comment: Broad specificity for glycerophosphodiesters; glycerophosphocholine, glycerophosphoethanolamine, glycerophosphoglycerol and bis(glycerophospho)-glycerol are hydrolysed.

references.title: Periplasmic glycerophosphodiester phosphodiesterase of Escherichia coli, a new enzyme of the glp regulon.
